TITLE: Expanding a Complex Task into Subtasks - Bash
DESCRIPTION: This bash code block provides commands to decompose a single task (by ID) into a specified number of subtasks, optionally guided by a prompt or using research-backed methods. Flags such as --num, --prompt, --all, and --research offer targeted and bulk subtask generation. Dependencies: Task Master AI must already have populated tasks.json and valid task IDs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master/blob/main/docs/tutorial.md#2025-04-23_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
task-master expand --id=5 --num=3

task-master expand --id=5 --prompt="Focus on security aspects"

task-master expand --all

task-master expand --id=5 --research
```

