TITLE: Defining Resource Read Request and Result Schemas
DESCRIPTION: Schemas for reading specific resources by URI. The request specifies the resource URI to read, and the result contains an array of resource contents (either text or binary blob formats).
SOURCE: https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master/blob/main/context/mcp-js-sdk-docs.txt#2025-04-23_snippet_204

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Sent from the client to the server, to read a specific resource URI.
 */
export const ReadResourceRequestSchema = RequestSchema.extend({
  method: z.literal("resources/read"),
  params: BaseRequestParamsSchema.extend({
    /**
     * The URI of the resource to read. The URI can use any protocol; it is up to the server how to interpret it.
     */
    uri: z.string(),
  }),
});

/**
 * The server's response to a resources/read request from the client.
 */
export const ReadResourceResultSchema = ResultSchema.extend({
  contents: z.array(
    z.union([TextResourceContentsSchema, BlobResourceContentsSchema]),
  ),
});
```

