TITLE: Abstract Capability Check Methods
DESCRIPTION: Abstract methods that must be implemented by subclasses to check if capabilities are supported for various operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master/blob/main/context/mcp-js-sdk-docs.txt#2025-04-23_snippet_174

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/**
 * A method to check if a capability is supported by the remote side, for the given method to be called.
 *
 * This should be implemented by subclasses.
 */
protected abstract assertCapabilityForMethod(
  method: SendRequestT["method"],
): void;

/**
 * A method to check if a notification is supported by the local side, for the given method to be sent.
 *
 * This should be implemented by subclasses.
 */
protected abstract assertNotificationCapability(
  method: SendNotificationT["method"],
): void;

/**
 * A method to check if a request handler is supported by the local side, for the given method to be handled.
 *
 * This should be implemented by subclasses.
 */
protected abstract assertRequestHandlerCapability(method: string): void;
```

