TITLE: Handling Connection Closure in JSON-RPC Protocol
DESCRIPTION: Method that handles connection closure by cleaning up resources and notifying handlers with a ConnectionClosed error.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master/blob/main/context/mcp-js-sdk-docs.txt#2025-04-23_snippet_167

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
private _onclose(): void {
  const responseHandlers = this._responseHandlers;
  this._responseHandlers = new Map();
  this._progressHandlers.clear();
  this._transport = undefined;
  this.onclose?.();

  const error = new McpError(ErrorCode.ConnectionClosed, "Connection closed");
  for (const handler of responseHandlers.values()) {
    handler(error);
  }
}
```

